05848nam a22008655i 9783034612623DE-B159720211129102213.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211129t20132009sz     fo  d z      eng d  a97830346126237 a10.1515/97830346126232doi  a(DE-B1597)207381  a(OCoLC)979688178  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aszcCH 4aTH4818.A3bM56 2009 7aARC0000002bisacsh04a720.471 aMinke, Gernot, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aBuilding with Earth :bDesign and Technology of a Sustainable Architecture /cGernot Minke.  a2nd rev. ed. 1aBasel : bBirkhäuser, c[2013] 4c©2009  a1 online resource (199 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tPreface -- tI The technology of earth building -- t1 Introduction -- t2 The properties of earth as a building material -- t3 Preparing of loam -- t4 Improving the earth’s characteristics by special treatment or additives -- t5 Rammed earthworks -- t6 Working with earth blocks -- t7 Large blocks and prefabricated panels -- t8 Direct forming with wet loam -- t9 Wet loam infill in skeleton structures -- t10 Tamped, poured or pumped lightweight loam -- t11 Loam plasters -- t12 Weather protection of loam surfaces -- t13 Repair of loam components -- t14 Designs of particular building elements -- t15 Earthquake-resistant building -- tII Built examples -- tResidences -- tCultural, Educational and Sacral Buildings -- tFuture prospects -- tMeasures -- tBibliographical references -- tAcknowledgements -- tIllustration credits0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDer ressourcenschonende und gesunde Baustoff Lehm, seit Jahrtausenden gebräuchlich, erfreut sich seit vielen Jahren auch in den Industrienationen wachsender Beliebtheit. In gemäßigten und trocken-heißen Klimazonen bietet der Lehm zahlreiche Vorteile gegenüber anderen Materialien. Seine spezifische Beschaffenheit und Textur ist außerdem von hohem ästhetischem Reiz. Die neue und erweiterte 2. Auflage dieses Handbuchs bietet einen praxisorientierten systematischen Überblick über die zahlreichen Einsatzmöglichkeiten und Verarbeitungstechniken von Lehm; seine Eigenschaften und physikalischen Gegebenheiten werden detailliert und kenntnisreich erläutert. Die reichhaltigen Erfahrungen, die der Autor bei der Ausführung von Lehmbauten im In- und Ausland über 30 Jahre gewinnen konnte, spiegeln sich in seiner Darstellung wieder. Zahlreiche Baustellenfotos und Zeichnungen zeigen die konkrete Umsetzung von Lehm-Architektur.  aFor a number of years, the healthy and environment-friendly building material earth, in common use for thousands of years, has been enjoying increasing popularity, including in industrialized nations. In hot dry and temperate climate zones, earth offers numerous advantages over other materials. Its particular texture and composition also holds great aesthetic appeal. The second and revised edition of this handbook offers a practical systematic overview of the many uses of earth and techniques for processing it. Its properties and physical characteristics are described in informed and knowledgeable detail. The author’s presentation reflects the rich and varied experiences gained over thirty years of building earth structures all over the world. Numerous photographs of construction sites and drawings show the concrete execution of earth architecture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aBuildingsxEnvironmental engineeringxElectronic books. 0aBuildingsxEnvironmental engineering. 0aEarth construction. 0aEarth houses. 0aSod houses. 0aSustainable architecture. 0aSustainable buildingsxDesign and construction. 4aLehm. 4aLehmbau. 7aARCHITECTURE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBo